      • doFrame

        public boolean doFrame(java.awt.Graphics g,
              int width,
              int height,
              boolean thruster,
              boolean rightArrow,
              boolean leftArrow,
              LunarX l,
              boolean landed,
              boolean started)
        Draws the rocket and adjusts its position based on the key strokes entered if the rocket has not landed yet.
        Parameters:
        g - the Graphics object
        width - the width of the game window
        height - the height of the game window
        thruster - true if the thruster is ignited (up arrow key being pressed)
        rightArrow - true if the right arrow key is being pressed
        leftArrow - true if the left arrow key is being pressed
        l - the LunarX game the rocket is in
        landed - true if the rocket is landed
        started - true if the game has already been started
        Returns:
        true if a change in the rocket in the frame has been made
